SIMPLE: nullify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nullify
<hw>Nul"li*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nullified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nullifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>nullificare</ets>; <ets>nullus</ets> none + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in
comp.) to make. See <er>Null</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>To make void; to render invalid; to deprive of
legal force or efficacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such correspondence would at once <qex>nullify</qex> the
conditions of the probationary system.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To abrogate; revoke; annul; repeal; invalidate;
cancel. See <er>Abolish</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nullipore</ent>⟦br⟧
